Stock

Class Item

  • java.lang.Object
    • Stock.Item

  • public class Item
extends java.lang.Object
    The Item class is an object used to hold properties about an Item that is stored within the stock. It is important to note that the toString method and the equals method have been overridden to allow comparisons. More on this below.
    Author:
    Matthew Topping

      • Item

        public Item(java.lang.String name,
            double manufacturingPrice,
            double sellPrice,
            int reorderPoint,
            int reorderAmount)
        This method constructs the Item object assignment the objects properties to it's appropriate private variables within the class
        Parameters:
        name - add a name to call the item. This will be used as the search key
        manfacturingPrice - add the cost to produce the item
        sellPrice - add the price at which the item will be sold
        reorderPoint - add an amount at which you wish to have this item reordered
        reorderAmount - add the amount of items that will be restocked when a reorder is called

      • Item

        public Item(java.lang.String name,
            double manufacturingPrice,
            double sellPrice,
            int reorderPoint,
            int reorderAmount,
            double storageTemp)
        This method constructs the Item in the same way as above but also adds an item storage temperature. This is used if the item is stored in a refrigerated unit.
        Parameters:
        storageTemp - this is a double that will hold the storage temperature of the object
